This paper is about language modeling, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and is typically classified under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques such as multinomial loss and non-negative matrix factorization, which are commonly used in areas such as machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with data sources and relevance, which are topics that are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and data management (cs.SD).
